					<head>Liturgy</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh98001892" rend="visible">
						<summary>A Karaite service-book according to the rite of Damascus.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jrb"> </textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh98001892">
							<locus from="1r" to="223v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sidur</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">סדור</title>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Seder_Karaim_1854"/>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">נשלם בעז' אלהי בחדש אלול משנת <date calendar="Hebrew">ה'ת'ס'</date> ליצי' והסימן י'ה'י'ה' ק'ד'ש' ל'א' יגאל והי <date calendar="Seleucid">שנת אלפים ואחד עשר לשטרות</date> ה' יכפיל שכר כותבו ומקדישו א'כ'י'ר'.<locus n="208v"/>
							</colophon>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="3v" to="16r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Introduction to the Karaite liturgy</title>
							<note>
								<p>No author's name is given not any authorities quoted in it; perhaps the treatise was authored by the scribe Daniel ben Mosheh Firuz. </p>
								<p>On folio 9v begins a list of Psalms and haftarot belonging to each pericope of the Pentateuch.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="16r" to="53r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Prayers for week-days</title>
							<note>
								<p>The evening service for the first week-day is missing entirely, as is the greater part of the morning service for the first day (about 45 leaves have been lost after folio 15).</p>
								<p>Services for the first day begin on folio 16r, services for evening and morning of the five other week-days, folio 35v.</p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Cf the contents of Or 2356, VI.</filiation>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="53r" to="99r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Sabbath-days</title>
							<note>
								<p>The evening prayer, folio 53r; the morning prayer, folio 60r; the afternoon prayer, folio 93v.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="99r" to="113v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for rosh ḥodesh</title>
							<note>
								<p>The evening prayer, folio 99r; the morning prayer, folio 104r; services for the Sabbath and rosh ḥodesh, folio 107v.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="113v" to="148r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for the season of Pesaḥ</title>
							<note>
								<p>The benediction of aviv, folio 113v; services corresponding to Halel ha-gadol, folio 114v; the ten plagues, folio 129v; then follow poetical pieces and Torah lections.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="148r" to="208v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for special Sabbaths</title>
							<note>
								<p>For Sabbath Be-shalaḥ, folio 148r; Ṿa-yishma῾, folio 159r; Purim, folio 170r; Ki tisa, folio 177r; Ekhah, folio 186r; Balaḳ, folio 187v; Shabat naḥamu, folio 188v; Ṿa-etḥanan, folio 197v; Kipur, folio 202v.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="209r" to="223v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Appendix</title>
							<note>
								<p>Five fragments of another copy of the same rite, with some differences (folios 209-211, 212, 213, 214-216, 217--223 respectively).</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the early 18th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>223 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>215</height>
										<width>150</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>165</height>
										<width>105</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>223 folios (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of originally 10 leaves each, signed with Hebrew letters.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Defective at the end.</p>
									<p>Leaves lost after folio 15, 106, 158, 205, 208, 211, 212, 213, 216. </p>
									<p>Four quires missing at the end. </p>
									<p>Stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="20 23" writtenLines="20 23">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Visible mastara ruling.</p>
									<p>Titles of sections written in larger characters.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="3">
							<summary>Oriental semi-cursive script, punctuated, of the early 18th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Daniel ben Mosheh ha-Melamed ben Yesh῾ayah Firuz</name>: inscribed, folio 3r.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole">
								<p>
									<locus from="209r" to="223v"/>: originally part of a different manuscript. Also, folio 2r, lines 3v-9v, appears to be in a different hand.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio 2r is a title page, and folio 3r begins with a dedication.</p>
							<p>Folios 219-223 are later additions.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
